event: The mouse is clicking on the "My Computer" icon on the desktop.
description: The user clicked the "My Computer" icon on the desktop. As a result, the "My Computer" window opened.
outcome: The "My Computer" window is open, displaying the contents of the "My Computer" directory, including drives and system folders. The "My Computer" icon on the taskbar is highlighted.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "Cdrom (D:)" icon within the "My Computer" window.
description: The user clicked the "Cdrom (D:)" icon within the "My Computer" window. As a result, the "Cdrom (D:)" window opened, displaying an empty drive.
outcome: The "Cdrom (D:)" window, displaying an empty drive, opened in front of the "My Computer" window and became the active window.  The taskbar added a button labeled "Cdrom (D:)".

event: The mouse pointer is hovering over the "cc32d479" file icon within the "Cdrom (D:)" window, and the user is clicking once.
description: The user clicks once on the "cc32d479.exe" file icon within the "Cdrom (D:)" window. As a result, the Netscape Communicator 4.79 setup window opens.
outcome: A Netscape Communicator 4.79 setup window replaced the previous window. The setup window displays a welcome message and recommends closing other programs before continuing. Two buttons, "Next >" and "Cancel," are available at the bottom of the window.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "Next>" button.
description: The user clicked the "Next >" button at the bottom of the "Netscape Communicator 4.79 Setup" window. As a result, the window transitioned to display the "Software License Agreement" screen.
outcome: The setup process transitioned to the "Software License Agreement" screen. The main window now displays the Netscape Client Products End-User License Agreement in a scrollable text box. The "Next" and "Cancel" buttons have been replaced with "< Back", "Yes", and "No" buttons.

event: The mouse is hovering over the "Yes" button in the "Software License Agreement" dialog box.
description: The user clicked the "Yes" button on the "Software License Agreement" dialog box.  As a result, the "Setup Type" window for Netscape Communicator 4.79 appears.
outcome: The "Software License Agreement" dialog box has been replaced with the "Setup Type" window. This window allows the user to choose between "Typical" and "Custom" installations, displays the destination directory ("C:\\Program Files\\Netscape\\Communicator"), and provides "Browse...", "< Back", "Next >", and "Cancel" buttons.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "Next >" button.
description: The user clicks the "Next >" button at the bottom of the "Setup Type" window. As a result, a "Question" dialog box appears, stating the chosen installation directory does not exist and prompting the user to create it.
outcome: The UI displays a dialog box titled "Question" that informs the user that the selected installation directory does not exist and asks if they would like to create it. The dialog box offers "Yes" and "No" buttons for the user to respond.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "Yes" button of the "Question" dialog box.
description: The user clicks the highlighted "Yes" button in the "Question" dialog box to confirm the creation of the "C:\Program Files\Netscape\Communicator" directory.
outcome: The UI transitioned to display the "Netscape Desktop Preference Options" dialog box. This dialog box presents three pre-checked options for the user to configure: making Netscape Communicator the default browser, setting Netscape.com as the home page, and using Netscape.com for web searches. The dialog box includes "Back", "Next", and "Cancel" buttons for navigation and control over these preferences.

event: The mouse pointer is hovering over the "Next >" button of the "Netscape Desktop Preference Options" window and the user is clicking the button.
description: The user clicked the "Next >" button at the bottom of the "Netscape Desktop Preference Options" window.  As a result, the "Select Program Folder" window appeared.
outcome: The "Netscape Desktop Preference Options" window was replaced with the "Select Program Folder" window. This new window features a text field for the "Program Folder," a list box labeled "Existing Folders," and instructions for selecting the installation directory. The "Next >" button is now inactive.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "Next >" button in the "Select Program Folder" window.
description: The user clicked the "Next >" button in the "Select Program Folder" window. This action advanced the installation process to the "Start Copying Files" window.
outcome: The "Select Program Folder" window was replaced by the "Start Copying Files" window. This new window provides details about the next step in the installation process, displays the chosen installation type ("Typical") and components, and features an "Install" button where the cursor is now positioned.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "Install >" button.
description: The user clicks the "Install" button to proceed with the installation using the "Typical" settings.  As a result, a "Question" dialog box appears, prompting the user for further input.
outcome: A dialog box titled "Question" appears with two buttons: "Yes" and "No". The "Yes" button has keyboard focus.

event: The mouse pointer is over the "No" button of the dialog box titled "Question".
description: The user clicked the "No" button on the "Question" dialog box. As a result, the "Question" dialog box was replaced with an "Information" dialog box.
outcome: A dialog box titled "Question" with "Yes" and "No" buttons was replaced with an "Information" dialog box. This new dialog box displays the message "Setup is complete. You may run Netscape Communicator 4.79 by double-clicking on one of the icons in the folder." and has an "OK" button.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "OK" button of the "Information" dialog box.
description: The user clicks the "OK" button on the "Information" dialog box.  As a result, the dialog box closes.
outcome: A modal dialog box that was previously present within the Netscape Communicator application is no longer visible.

event: The mouse dragged the Netscape Communicator window.
description: The user clicked and dragged the title bar of the Netscape Communicator window to move its position on the screen.

event: The mouse is clicking on the close button of the window titled "Netscape Communicator".
description: The user clicks the close button (✕) in the title bar of the "Netscape Communicator" window.  As a result, the window closes and is minimized to the taskbar as "Netscape Co...".
outcome: The "Netscape Communicator" window that was previously visible is no longer present, replaced by a minimized window titled "Netscape Co..." on the taskbar.

event: The mouse is clicking on the close button of the window titled "Cdrom (D:)".
description: The user clicks the close button (✕) on the "Cdrom (D:)" window. As a result, the window is closed.
outcome: The "Cdrom (D:)" window has been closed and a new icon, "Netscape Communicator", has appeared on the desktop.

event: The mouse pointer is hovering over the desktop background and will click the desktop.
description: The mouse pointer clicks on the empty space of the Windows 98 desktop.

event: The mouse pointer is clicking on the Netscape Communicator desktop shortcut.
description: The user clicked the "Netscape Communicator" shortcut icon on the Windows 98 desktop.  This resulted in the appearance of a "Creating a New Profile" dialog box.
outcome: A dialog box titled "Creating a New Profile" appeared on the Windows 98 desktop. The dialog box explains that Netscape Communicator stores user settings and suggests creating a profile. It includes "< Back", "Next >", "Finish", and "Cancel" buttons.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "Next >" button in the "Creating a New Profile" dialog box.
description: The user clicked the "Next >" button in the "Creating a New Profile" dialog box.  As a result, the dialog box progressed to the "Enter Your Name and Email Address" screen.
outcome: The "Enter Your Name and Email Address" dialog box within the Netscape Communicator profile creation process is displayed. The "Next >" button is highlighted.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Shift_L', 'B'].
description: The user pressed the keyboard shortcut 'Shift + B', which corresponds to the underlined character in the "Next >" button label.  Nothing visually changes in the UI as a result of this action.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['o'].
description: The user typed the letter "o" into the "Full Name" field.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['b'].
description: The user pressed the 'b' key, which is the hotkey for the "< Back" button. However, no change in the dialog box is observed.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['space'].
description: The user pressed the 'space' key. No visible changes occurred in the GUI.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['Shift_L', 'A'].
description: The user typed the letter "A" into the "Full Name" field within the "Enter your Name and Email Address" dialog box.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['l', 'i'].
description: The user typed the letters "li" into the "Full Name:" text field.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['c', 'e'].
description: The user typed the letters "ce" into the "Email Address:" field.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['s'].
description: The user typed the letter "s" into the "Full Name:" field.

event: The key following key(s) were pressed: ['o', 'n'].
description: The user typed the letters "on" into the "Full Name:" field.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "Next >" button inside a dialog box.
description: The user clicks the "Next >" button in the "Enter your Name and Email Address" dialog box. As a result, the dialog box is replaced with the "Choose a Name and Directory for your Profile" dialog box.
outcome: The "Choose a Name and Directory for your Profile" dialog box within the Netscape Communicator profile creation process is displayed. The dialog box contains a "Profile Name" text field with the word "default" entered, a text field displaying the directory "C:\\Program Files\\Netscape\\Users\\d", and four buttons: "< Back", "Next >", "Finish", and "Cancel". The "Next >" button is highlighted.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "Next >" button in the "Choose a Name and Directory for your Profile" dialog box.
description: The user clicks the "Next >" button in the "Choose a Name and Directory for your Profile" dialog box. As a result, the dialog box is replaced with the "Set up your Outgoing Mail Server" dialog box.
outcome: The "Choose a Name and Directory for your Profile" dialog box was replaced with a new dialog box titled "Set up your Outgoing Mail Server". This new dialog box contains a text field pre-filled with the word "mail", and the buttons "< Back", "Next >", "Finish", and "Cancel", with the "Next >" button highlighted.

event: The mouse is clicking on the "Finish" button in the "Set up your Outgoing Mail Server" dialog box.
description: The user clicks the "Finish" button at the bottom of the "Set up your Outgoing Mail Server" dialog box. This results in an error message stating "Netscape is unable to locate the server home.netscape.com."
outcome: The "Set up your Outgoing Mail Server" dialog box was replaced with a "Netscape" dialog box. This new dialog box displays an error message stating "Netscape is unable to locate the server home.netscape.com. Please check the server name and try again." and has an "OK" button.

event: The mouse is clicking on the OK button of a pop-up window titled "Netscape".
description: The user clicks the "OK" button on the "Netscape" pop-up window, dismissing the error message "Netscape is unable to locate the server home.netscape.com. Please check the server name and try again."
outcome: The "Netscape" pop-up window disappeared, and the bottom of the main window now displays the error message "Unable to locate host home.netscape.com."
